(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["FtpBooster"],{"51b9":function(e,t,a){"use strict";var n=a("5b0a"),o=a.n(n);o.a},"5b0a":function(e,t,a){},afdf:function(e,t,a){e.exports=a.p+"img/ftp_booster.c930469b.png"},ed3d:function(e,t,a){"use strict";a.r(t);var n=function(){var e=this,t=e.$createElement;e._self._c;return e._m(0)},o=[function(){var e=this,t=e.$createElement,n=e._self._c||t;return n("div",[n("img",{staticClass:"cover-image",attrs:{src:a("afdf")}}),n("div",{staticClass:"container"},[n("h1",[e._v("From 3.7 w/kg to 4.5 w/kg in a Month")]),n("p",[e._v("At the beginning of this winter I finally jumped onto the Zwift hype train and invested in an Elite Rampa\n            Smart trainer. After spending most of October, November and December not doing any riding I was nowhere\n            near\n            the shape I was in the summer, so to regain some fitness I fully committed myself to the Zwift 4 week\n            FTP\n            boosting plan. After a full month of riding almost everyday I saw my FTP increase from 240 watts\n            (3.7w/kg)\n            to 292 watts (4.5w/kg).")]),n("h2",[e._v("A bit of Background")]),n("p",[e._v("There are two factors that probably contributed to my 50 watt gain. Firstly, although I didn’t do an FTP\n            test, based on how hard efforts felt, I’d estimate my FTP was around 275 in late September. Secondly I\n            spent most of October, November, and December rock climbing, so although my body weight had remained at\n            65kg my muscle was redistributed from my lower body to upper body.")]),n("h2",[e._v("The Initial FTP Test")]),n("p",[e._v("I did the "),n("a",{staticClass:"default",attrs:{href:"https://www.strava.com/activities/1327137053"}},[e._v("initial FTP test")]),e._v(" on\n            Christmas day (before the big turkey) and managed to push out 260 watts for\n            20 minutes. The effort hurt in a way different to what I remembered FTP efforts feeling like. It was\n            mainly my lungs holding me back and although my legs felt like they could go a bit harder, my lungs felt\n            like they couldn’t take in enough oxygen and I was tasting blood in the back of my throat. It was\n            disappointing to see how much fitness I had lost in 3 months, but it motivated me to start riding again,\n            and I set a goal to get my FTP up to 270 watts by the end of the month long training block.")]),n("h2",[e._v("Week 1")]),n("p",[e._v("Being a bit of an egomaniac I refused to believe how much fitness, so I immediately manually bumped my\n            FTP settings up to 250 to make the workouts harder. The first workout was incredibly hard and part of me\n            was wishing I had just kept the settings at 240, but I made it through in the end.")]),n("p",[e._v("One of the first things I learned in the first week is that erg mode is useless for efforts less than 1\n            minute.")]),n("p",[e._v("I was riding everyday, and sticking to the plan religiously but I had to shuffle the order of my rides\n            sometimes since I work 9am-5pm and have class from 7pm-10pm on Mondays and Wednesdays. This allowed me\n            to do the shorter rides on Monday and Wednesday and save the long rides for the other days. When you\n            only have an hour at home between work and class, a 45 minute workout at least gives you 15 minutes to\n            shower and get out the door.")]),n("h2",[e._v("Week 2")]),n("p",[e._v("The workouts were still hard but I was feeling a bit better by the end of my efforts. So naturally I\n            raised the FTP setting up to 260 because feeling good, especially at the end of a workout is overrated.\n            The first workout after bumping up the settings hurt so much…as expected, and near the end I had that\n            nagging thought in my head again that I had bitten off more than I could chew. But, like last time I\n            managed to pull through and get to the end all while keeping the contents of my stomach, firmly in my\n            stomach (for the most part).")]),n("p",[e._v("The rest of the week seemed to go by quickly although there were a couple of days where it took an\n            enormous amount of will-power just to plug in my trainer and launch Zwift. But, I new that the feeling\n            of regret if I missed a day would kill me, so I just sucked it up and rode.")]),n("h2",[e._v("Week 3")]),n("p",[e._v("Another week, another 10 watts added to the FTP settings so I could feel like dying by the end of the\n            workout on the first day. Just kidding…I kept the 260 watt setting from the previous week, maybe it was\n            because I was still finding the workouts difficult, or maybe it was because I was growing soft.")]),n("p",[e._v("At this point I had run out of new years motivation and the main reason why I stuck with the plan was\n            fear of being dropped by friends on rides in the summer. It felt like I had been riding a lot but I’d\n            only been putting in 7 hours a week which is less than what I would normally do in the summer. That\n            realization made things seem a bit more manageable and made the training plan seem a bit less\n            mental.")]),n("h2",[e._v("Week 4")]),n("p",[e._v("This was the final week so I bumped the FTP settings on the workouts up to 270, with hopes of if I could\n            do these workouts it meant my FTP was somewhere near 270. This week actually had a rest day which I\n            scheduled to Friday so I could go to a bar and do some carb loading with friends. I also added an\n            additional rest day on Monday so I wouldn’t have to worry about the timing of my night class.")]),n("p",[e._v("One of the sessions before the FTP test includes a 10 minute max effort to help you gauge what your 20\n            minute effort might be. I averaged 320 watts for 10 minutes and felt really good at the end, so I was\n            super psyched and realized I would probably be able to blow my 270 watt goal out of the water.")]),n("h2",[e._v("The FTP Test")]),n("p",[e._v("When the day came to finally do the "),n("a",{staticClass:"default",attrs:{href:"https://www.strava.com/activities/1383924699"}},[e._v("FTP test")]),e._v("\n            the Zwift course was London so I had to go into the Zwift\n            config file and change the course to Watopia since I wanted to go up a mountain for extra motivation. My\n            initial goal was to increase my FTP to 270, but after that 10 minute effort at 320 watts I was getting\n            greedy and wanted to do 310 watts for the 20 minutes.")]),n("p",[e._v("At the beginning of the FTP effort, I was really struggling to find a rhythm and appropriate gearing. It\n            felt like I was either doing 350 watts at 80 rpm or 300 watts at 105 rpm but this was probably a mental\n            thing more than anything. At the 10 minute mark a message pops up on the screen saying you’re halfway\n            there and to add 10 more watts if you feel good. I did not feel good. Despite averaging 10 watts less\n            than my previous 10 minute effort I was feeling terrible and was convinced I wouldn’t make it. I backed\n            off my power a bit and let the average drop down to 305. In the last 3 minutes I was suffering in ways I\n            haven’t suffered before, my right arm was going numb, and I was fighting to hold back my vomit.")]),n("p",[e._v("When I crossed the line I had nothing left in me, but when I ended the ride to see my new FTP at 292\n            watts, I couldn’t help but smile and feel relieved that all the pain over the past 4 weeks was worth it.\n            I’m only 21 so I have a lot of life left to experience, but that moment alone in my basement, dripping\n            in sweat was one of the best so far.")]),n("h2",[e._v("Closing Remarks")]),n("p",[e._v("Riding almost everyday is not only logistically challenging, but also mentally exhausting. During the month I was only climbing once a week and I did notice a bit of loss of upper body strength (especially while looking in the mirror). I’m now moving onto my next training block which will be focused more on endurance and will probably only be 4-5 rides a week but more volume. I’m also looking forward to being able to dedicate some more time to climbing.")]),n("p",[e._v("If you want to see how my endurance training is going follow me on "),n("a",{staticClass:"default",attrs:{href:"https://www.strava.com/athletes/5114942"}},[e._v("Strava")]),e._v(".")])])])}],i={name:"FtpBooster"},s=i,r=(a("51b9"),a("2877")),h=Object(r["a"])(s,n,o,!1,null,"5e7ed059",null);h.options.__file="FtpBooster.vue";t["default"]=h.exports}}]);
